    </div>
    <div class="container-text-1 col-md-6" style="width: 70%; height: 40%">
        <p>
            <h3>So, what is a family budget?</h3>
        </p>
        <p>
            A family budget is a plan for your household’s incoming and outgoing money over a certain period of time,
            such as a month or year. For example, you may aim for certain dollar amounts or percentages of your
            combined monthly income to go toward various expenses, like groceries, as well as saving, investing and paying off debt.
        </p>
        <p>
            Many people simply spend their income without being intentional about it, she says, but you get to decide how to allocate that
            money so that it works for you.
        </p>
        <p>So let’s make a plan for you.</p>
    </div>
</div>
